  "text": "From the numerical study, we have also seen how the fitness of bacteria and viruses shows different thermal responses, even for the same number of rate determining genes and the same metabolic reaction free energy barrier. This is primarily because high mutation rate in RNA viruses results in less stable proteins than those of DNA-based organisms as suggested also in recent empirical observations [CITATION_1] ).",
